[b]Oscillator Divergence Zones[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Finds regular and hidden divergences by comparing consecutive price pivot lows and highs with the corresponding oscillator values. Regular bullish divergence fires when price makes a lower low while the oscillator makes a higher low; bearish when price makes a higher high while the oscillator makes a lower high. Hidden divergences signal trend continuation rather than reversal. Each confirmed signal creates an ATR-wide horizontal price zone that stays active until the structure fully breaks — giving you a persistent reference level rather than a one-bar flash.

[b]Oscillator[/b]
[list]
[*]RSI (default) — standard momentum oscillator, OB/OS at 70/30
[*]CCI — centered on 0, OB/OS at 100/−100; update filter thresholds to ~±25 when switching
[*]MFI — volume-weighted, OB/OS at 80/20; requires volume data
[/list]

[b]Visualization[/b]
[list]
[*]Oscillator pane: gradient-colored oscillator line, fills between the oscillator and the midline (50 for RSI/MFI, 0 for CCI), and labeled markers at each divergence pivot
[*]Oscillator pane: dotted connector lines between consecutive pivot values for regular divergences; dashed lines at reduced opacity for hidden divergences; small triangle markers distinguish the two types
[*]Chart overlay: labeled markers at the price pivot bar ("Reversal" for regular, "Cont." for hidden) and horizontal zones that extend into the future until broken
[*]Regular zones: solid edge, semi-transparent fill. Hidden zones: dashed edge, transparent fill
[*]Broken zones switch to dotted edge and gray fill — structural history without cluttering active signals
[/list]

[b]Divergence Detection[/b]
[list]
[*]Pivots are detected on price (not on the oscillator) — the correct approach for standard divergence; the oscillator is used only for momentum confirmation
[*]Only consecutive pivots within a configurable minimum and maximum bar range are compared, filtering out noise and excessively wide spans
[*]Optional OB/OS filter suppresses signals in the neutral oscillator zone
[*]Break trigger is configurable: full-candle through level (wick-resistant, default) or close-based
[/list]

[b]Zone Retest Counter[/b]
Each active zone tracks how many times price re-enters it without breaking. The count is displayed as ×N at the right edge of the zone and includes a hover tooltip explaining the metric.

[b]Alerts[/b]
Four alert conditions are included — bullish divergence, bearish divergence, bullish hidden divergence, bearish hidden divergence — each with ticker and timeframe in the message. Alerts fire via both named alertcondition() (separate setup per type) and alert() (single "any alert() call" setup covers all four).

